  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators hypothesize that NBI will have a high accuracy in predicting polyp
      histology real time during a colonoscopy by visualization of the surface mucosal and vascular
      patterns. Aim#1: To determine the sensitivity, specificity and accuracy of NBI and standard
      white light colonoscopy for predicting polyp histology by evaluating the surface mucosal and
      vascular patterns during colonoscopy. Aim#2: To determine the inter-observer agreement
      between investigators for the recognition of various polyp patterns.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
